title.narrative: Filling implementation gaps in the National HIV and AIDS response towards achievement of accelerated universal access in Sierra Leone

description.narrative: Sierra Leone - HIV - National HIV/AIDS Secretariat - NAS. This program has the following goals: To prevent HIV/AIDS, provide treatment, care and support, as well as mitigate its socio-economic impact at both national and sub-national levels in Sierra Leone. The objectives of this program are: Strengthen and expand national capacity to design, implement, monitor and evaluate levels and trends of HIV infections among the general population and population sub groups and collect and analyse data and disseminate strategic information. Provide quality home-based care and improve the capacity of families and communities to provide care and support for PLHIVs and OVCs. Provide Comprehensive HIV Care including antiretroviral Therapy (ART ) to adults and children with advanced HIV Infection. Improve access to and utilization of HIV Counseling and Testing (HCT) services nationwide. Develop and implement a new partnership framework for multi-sectoral and multidisciplinary national response at all levels. Prevention, care support and treatment programs expanded from one to four high risk groups nationwide.. Promote improved health seeking behaviour and adoption of safer sex practise through BCC messages. Provide prophylactic treatment to HIV positive women and their new borns, and promote safe delivery and other maternal services
